annotation.TEXT: Okay, here comes a full run, from the start of the level, and none of this will be sped up.
Alright, here's where I hit the coin cap, which is indeed 9999.
And then that happens... Well, I saw Air Bound mages there, so it's obvious how I'm meant to go up.
There's the Tea Time lady, and a Fire-using bunairpire, which I'll quickly dispatch.
Okay, now I may have hit that switch way too early there, but I figured out something I can do, and that is wait for the timer to run out, then hit that same switch again!
I'm not even gonna stop to kill that cave now.
There's a Charge Buster bunny here. Maybe I could take that, but I really want to hold onto the Ball + Air Bound combo right now.
Now, there's a Slow Down mage. I wonder if that would be worth getting... But, I'll once again just stick with Ball and Air Bound.
There we go! Oh, but all that's here is a checkpoint and 20 coins. Too bad it's not like a shortcut or anything.
That's an 8-tile jump, and Air Bound alone only gets me 7 tiles of height. I'd need to either bounce off of one of those duders that were up there, or use Ball with Air Bound.
World 6-7, Lunarian Tower, start!
And yes, I've ditched Ball there, since I NEED to be able to quickly get Magical Arrow at that one spot during this autoscroller. At least I don't think I'll need Ball anymore.
Blue wizard needs yams badly.
Yeah, I have no idea how to avoid those bunnies. I've never successfully dodged them ever since that first time.
However, if the missing spell could've been found in any of the levels I've already cleared, you can tell me that. Just don't say what the spell is.
Ooh, a 1-up. Okay, I hope I'm getting close to the end of this place...
I don't suppose I can make the Ball bunny that I didn't kill respawn up there, can I?
Hit the guy already! Man, I wasted too much time here...
Okay, that's everyone... except, now there's a Fire mage shooting at me from a higher ledge.
Too bad the wind is coming from the maids, and not a Wind mage, I don't think.
Well, it's obvious what I need to do there now, but I just didn't think fast enough there, and when I realized what needed to be done, it was too late.
Ooh, Sniper. Now that's tempting. But, I'm afraid of running into another 8-tile wall that I'll need Ball + Air Bound to get past.
It's not a moon door, so no boss yet, but...
Oh, I see this trick. I need to hit that spring.
Now, by going up this way, I can avoid that cheap trick, but will the game pull another?
Okay, I've decided to grab Ball here, which I think will greatly help with that spot up above, so that I won't need the purple angel bunnies.
Now, I'm thinking of doing something else before heading to world EX-1, but what will that something be? Find out next time! To be continued... Yo!
Die, Galbo. (I got its name correct this time, right?)
Ball is a good way to take out that sword.
That is NOT the time for blatant trial-and-error gameplay in an autoscroller, game!
That's a fail. I think I had triggered the first blue switch way too early on that run, and then the second Bomb bunny blew up before I could stomp it.
Whoa, I'm surprised the hand didn't hit me there when I grazed the top of its fingers.
Well, there's yet another checkpoint sign that didn't proudly proclaim "CHECKPOINT!", but as I'd shown in the past, they still do work properly when that happens.
Whoa, there are a couple archers too. Now, I doubt I'll need Ice or Magical Arrow, but if it turns out I'm wrong, I'll restart the level as usual.
Also, if I had given up Ball earlier, I could've gotten it back here.
Okay, let's cut to the autoscrolling part again.
Whoa, what? Isn't that the Tea Time medal that popped out of that block? And, that would be a very bad thing to grab during an autoscroller, so I'd better avoid it.
Uh, oh. I hit the switch early again. But, that might not matter too much now.
More Ground Spark mages. Of course, I can just Ground Spark them back!
I like that I can still easily make that jump even if I bump my head on the mages' box above.
When it comes to multiple timer switches of the same type in quick succession, when you trigger later ones, it adds to the currently remaining time from previous ones.
Still gotta gobble up some of those coins, since I can.
Nice. By not shooting a Bomb bunny that time, I was able to "bunny hop" to this chain this time.
Ow. That jump is quite tricky.
Hello, and welcome back to Tobari! Today, I'll be taking on that tower to the moon that I unlocked last time. But first, I noticed something in my Steam achievements...
Ditching Ground Spark now to make room for Ball in a moment.
BTW, those 18 coins there... totally not worth the trouble.
Nope, couldn't make use of the Bomb bunnies...
Somehow, I stomped one of those purple angel bunnies instead of hitting it directly with the Ball.
Now, what I like to do here now is go down one way, stomp the angel bunny there, then go back up and drop down the other side to stomp the other one.
I think I'll go down this way instead of trying to land in between the spikes. There are columns I can land on to the sides of the Air Bound mages.
Oh, come on. That hit me?
Now, I believe I've been told that this level has no moon shard for me to worry about, so I just have to focus on clearing the level and that's it.
Okay, I'm back here, where I'm purchasing Shoot Rock just before that room again.
Whoa, what? Another Rinka shooter tried to ambush me there!
And, here we have a ghostly hand and snakes. This level is just mix-and-matching enemies from various places.
DOUBLE KILL! Nice. The Arrow is certainly more useful here than Fire.
Umm... Okay... If you burn away the vine that archer is standing on, the archer just stays standing in midair. Apparently, they don't believe in the law of gravity.
And, there's two more checkpoints that are just 5 seconds from each other. Also, a shop.
Well, with Ball, I can go up a little bit, but it looks like I really will need to get Air Bound below in order to go further.
Alright, these spells together have decent coverage. However, if I see better spells later, I may swap these out, especially if such spells are required for something.
That wasn't a golden broom-rider, so I couldn't have gotten Broom from it. Of course, Broom wouldn't help with vertical climbing.
Wow, I'm getting sloppy here. Well, I believe I saw two hearts with the Air Bound mages, so those'll help.
Aw, nuts! I shouldn't have shot that first Bomb bunny...
It's not looking like it. I bet it rolled off the bottom of the playfield off-screen, which made the game declare it dead, so it'll never respawn. So... I've gotta restart again.
Oh, no! What?!
Oh, man... The stairs for this climbing segment are different than usual. I'm sure I'm approaching the end of the tower.
Nice, I made it up here this time!
Oh, I'd love to get Wind here, but I'm not risking it! Just try not to get knocked off!
Uh, oh. I hope I didn't waste too much time here...
Okay, I didn't hit the switch earlier than usual this time. Maybe that will help me at the part where I fell last time.
Hmm... I could get Magical Arrow, Ice, or Fire here, but... nah. I still want to keep Ball and Air Bound.
Perfect! And wow, that switch had a short time limit. You absolutely needed to hit it from long-distance.
Whoa, and suddenly, the tower level is over and I'm at World EX! Now, there's no "PREV WORLD" level dot here, but there still is the World Select, fortunately.
Oh, man. The game's offering me Thunder now. Ooh... so tempting... If I knew for sure that there was a boss just ahead, I'd take it, but I have no idea if there will be a boss...
Gotcha. Okay, I see a Tea Time lady and a bunch of other duders up there.
But, I'll sit in this World Select and let you guys listen to this new music for a few minutes if you want.
Yamnomnom.
Hmm... I think I should shoot that switch with an arrow. What do you guys think? Place your votes now, and we'll find out next time! ...Wait, no. I'll just shoot it.
Whoa, speedy bunny.
I do see Fire and Ground Spark being used by mages up there, and I'll want to grab one of each.
Wait, was I supposed to bounce off of one of those purple angel bunnies to get up from here? Argh... Wish I had known that sooner...
Oh, sure. NOW Shoot Rock is available. Well... I guess I'll take it, and remove Magical Arrow for it.
Not gonna bother with out-of-the-way non-essential things, like that first checkpoint.
And Rinkas, and now birds too. Ball will keep me safe from the birds at least.
Ha! Dodged them all!
You won't hear the jump sound effect when you do that, but who cares? Okay, so let's kill this cave here...
And... I hate to say it, but I don't think I can continue upward with just Air Bound...
Pfft... How did I manage to screw up that simple jump?
Whoa, geez! ...Wow!
So much electricity in the air here.
It's the Jellied Yam shop, so it could very well be boss time! (Also, why does it make the "ka-ching" noise when it doesn't actually let me buy any more Jellied Yams?)
Ow, whatever. There's the heart right there.
It still looks like there's a slot for an 8th world in these, though. (World PH, as in Phantasm, perhaps?)
Okay, I'm low on health, so I'm gonna try to spare the Tea Time lady while clobbering everyone else up here.
Nice, I took exactly enough hits for all the hearts in this room to be useful, and finish it with full health.
Oh, wow. The game's providing me with multiple 1-ups for free here. Am I nearing the end? A boss, perhaps?
Yeah, that's just coins, not a heart.
I think I'll ditch Ball to try to get Magical Arrow here.
Nuts to that 1-up.
Oh, what?! How did I manage to screw that up?! Grumble... Grumble...
Okay, climb steadily but carefully...
No, we aren't done with the regular gameplay yet! Oh, man! Elevator action!
OMNOMNOM!
There's some more Rinka shooters.
Also, I think someone told me that Spark has a higher DPS than even Thunder. Maybe I'll try that on a boss in the future.
Whoa! I'm surprised I slipped through those bunnies without getting hit somehow. Anyway, we have an autoscrolling section here, and those often make me nervous.
Pfft... That's okay, since there's a heart right here.
Oh, what? Huh... I thought Tea Time was a full heal, but nope. It just heals 2 hearts (which is a full heal without any Jellied Yams).
There is still a checkpoint up here, though, along with a shop this time. Maybe I'm nearing the end...? Perhaps there's a boss coming up...?
MULTI KILL!
And here's where I took a dumb hit. I'll just go back down a bit and grab the heart by the ghost hand.
Whoa, bunny parade. Ball will make short work of them, though.
Darn real life interruptions. Sorry about that. Okay, where was I? Oh, yeah. Dealing with this cave.
Okay, get ready. It's just after I hop across the three flying duders here.
Oh, I hope triggering that switch earlier than usual doesn't screw me over...
Okay, I gotta be faster here this time.
So, what I need to do when I get to that point is quickly ditch one of my spells so I can grab Magical Arrow, then shoot the green switch with it.
Hmm... Maybe I should've just left her standing there in midair, in case I decided I did want Magical Arrow later. Well, whatever.
However, this time, I intend to keep Ball so that I can combine it with Air Bound up above. So, Shoot Rock won't get used for very long.
Ow, whatever. There are hearts here, so I don't care about that hit. Okay, let's go up there with the Ball + Air Bound combo this time!
There we go! I'm sure I didn't need to bounce off an enemy in addition to using these spells, but whatever.
I wasn't really much faster, and the purple angel bunnies weren't in a good spot for me this time anyway... Nuts!
Hey there, Ice mages. How's it going?
WAH! I just jumped right into that one. Huh, a bunairpire that shoots rocks. I don't think I've seen one of those before. And, once again, I want to keep Ball + Air Bound.
And yep, there's another two checkpoints within 5 seconds of each other.
Okay, for realsies this time!
...What?! NO!!! The game's pulling that stunt, this far into a long level?! Not cool!
Yep, the angel bunnies weren't in the right spot, and now I'm boned.
Yep! And, the guy killed himself, which is just as well, since I don't want Crash Star anyway. Oh, hey. Two hearts here. That's perfect, since I just took two hits.
Apparently, the Crash Star mage doesn't kill himself if I make him go far enough off-screen in time.
And, by doing that, I should have more than enough time to reach the chain past the Bomb bunnies without any issues.
Zap! Well, there's still 3 more hearts that can be grabbed before the end of this room, and if I somehow take further damage, I can buy Plum Tea at a shop coming up.
Yeah, maybe it's kind of a waste of 50 coins, but I'm getting fairly close to 9999 coins, which I think is the cap, and Shoot Rock lets me hit some foes here more easily.
I'm going to try to avoid killing the Tea Time lady if I can.
Whoa, spikes. At least they're not red spikes.
Okay... I've made it back here again. This time, I know which way to go at that spot, but now I'm worried it'll pull that stunt again.
Pfft... Well, that's an auto-mulligan. I should've reacted faster there.
Nope, still can't use the Bomb bunnies there.
Pfft... And I get hit anyway.
Yeah, can't take Tea Time since that would cost me one of my vital spells.
Excellent. With Ball, I don't need those angel bunnies at all, and getting up here is quite easy.
So, you'll want to hit them all to maximize your amount of switch time. I believe this is also true of these switches in Amapani and Urapani.
Whoa, new music, and it's epic-sounding!
Alright, after a quick pause break to make sure that little half-minute recording segment didn't screw up (I'm often paranoid about that), it's time to take on this tower!
Cut it kind of close there. Yeah, I don't want to hit that last switch way too early.
Okay, the cave has been dealt with. What's next?
Uhh... For some reason, I neglected to enter the shop this time.
And here's the Air Bound + Ball combo that I'll be keeping until I reach the fast autoscrolling section again.
Alright, let's see if I can maybe not fall into the abyss in this room this time.
Still made it no problem with just Air Bound.
You know what? I think I will grab Magical Arrow here, swapping out Fire for it.
Yep, a Ball-powered jump by itself gives me just less than 6 tiles worth of height, which is how high the next pair of ledges is.
Ditch Magical Arrow for Shoot Rock as usual here.
Did I just see... Crash Star?
Maybe I should've just accepted the death there and restarted from the checkpoint, but then I'd be lacking Air Bound and Ball.
Ack. Whatever.
Awesome, I sniped that guy before he could launch a single Ground Spark.
Okay, so there are signs pointing both up and down here. Hmm... I don't think I can go up right now. Maybe I should've picked up Ball earlier in that autoscrolling section.
Ow, more sloppiness...
Yeah, reached the chain with plenty of time to spare.
Oh, no... This is no boss, but instead, a faster autoscroller! I already don't like this!
And, there's a Rinka shooter. Too bad there's no actual Rinka magic medal that I can use.
I somehow didn't get hit there.
BTW, interesting trick when it comes to jumping from chains/ladders. If you're holding the jump button, you'll automatically do a full jump upon climbing off the side of them.
And yeah, why not? I'll buy a save too.
DOUBLE KILL! Whoa, I wasn't expecting that. Okay, I only need one Air Bound.
Oh, no checkpoint at the start of the climbing segment this time? What a shock!
Bah. I wonder how you're supposed to get past those bunnies without getting hit...
Uhh... Can I even reach that ledge? Oh, please don't tell me I screwed up again!
I figured I'd just cut out most of the repeat stuff.
Um, yeah, I should enter the door before it's too late. At least I was able to claim a good chunk of those coins.
I wonder if maybe there's an upward-attacking spell like Shoot Rock available before this point... I don't recall seeing any such spell, though...
How did I let myself get hit there? Well, since I still haven't figured out a sure-fire way to avoid the bunnies at the start of the first autoscroller, I'd better not get hit again now!
Wait... I don't need two Fire medals, silly.
This looks mighty tricky. Maybe Broom would've been helpful here... if it was available, that is.
Meh, whatever.
Yeah, I can get 8 tiles of height by combining Ball with Air Bound.
Wow, even more new music! Well, let's do the usual thing and see what all of the World Selects look like now.
Oh, I can see the ledge with the next checkpoint above. So, all these stair-climbing segments are part of the same section, it seems.
Oh, someone's tossing Ice up there. Also, there are some vines to burn.
Wait, what? Another checkpoint already? But the previous one was just 5 seconds back! Why have two checkpoints so close together with no major hazards in between?
Oh, and despite my spending at shops within the level, I have been making money in the long run, and am getting very close to the 9999-coin cap. I'll likely hit it on this run.
Wow, two obviously dumb hits there. I hope I'm not heading straight into a boss battle now without a chance to heal...
Gimme your yams!
Alright, that's all of them, and I'm gonna end off the episode here.
Okay, this dudette uses Fire, which I don't think I need. (Watch there be a wall of vines just up ahead now.)
Yeah, I jumped right into that arrow. Whatever, I've still got 5 HP left. Now, time for some timer switch shenanigans.
Ooh, Jellied Yams. Even more reason not to grab that Tea Time medal, even if I was injured.
Man... I wish I'd seen that tall wall coming sooner.
Okay, I'm able to snipe that Ground Spark mage sooner than before. That may help.
Now, according to my Steam achievements, I've found 24/25 of the spells so far. IDK what the 25th spell is yet, but please don't spoil it for me. I'd like to discover it myself.
That was interesting how I took out that archer with one of my Ground Sparks, fired several seconds ago.
Okay, they've been dealt with. Now for this cave...
Bingo! The Joy of Shopping! That's for spending a total of 10,000 coins at shops. I had noticed that I'd spent 9575 before this episode, so I just bought 9 1-ups to hit 10K.
COINS!!! And Bomb bunnies!
Well, let's see if I can heal with Tea Time while the Fire mage is hopefully far enough off-screen to not attack.
Okay, I took a careless extra hit there, but if I can make it to the shop, and remember to enter it, I'll be fine.
Whoa, what's with the cracks? Is the sky falling? Is an Ultra Beast going to appear?
Hey there, Rinka shooters. How's it going?
There's another cave, which appears to be producing purple angel bunnies. Well, Ball should keep me completely safe from them.
Oh, man. Rinkas.
Oh, there's an Ice Galbo among the duders up there, which I didn't notice last time. But, I don't think Ice would help me here.
